The paper deals with recommendation systems, which is a subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of side information suggests that the paper may also fall under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) or natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper may be relevant to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI) due to the collaborative filtering signals used in the method. Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of computers and society (cs.CY) due to the potential ethical implications of recommendation systems.
